A bibliophile's dream via @madelinestraveling 📚 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @planetfervor

More than 70,000 books make this library in its hall, Admont Abbey Library in Austria a truly a book lover's paradise!

The Admont Abbey Library is an Austria-based monastic library located in Admont, a small town next to the Enns River in Austria, and is attached to the Admont Abbey. Admont Abbey Library is the largest monastic library in the world, and is noted for its Baroque art, architecture and manuscripts.

Tag your book lover's friends!

📽 @madelinestraveling
📍 Admont Abbey Library, Austria
🎶 Wildest Dreams - Duomo

node.text:
The Marieta Islands are a group of small uninhabited islands a few miles off the coast of Mexico 😍 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on planetfervor.com (link in my bio: @planetfervor)

One of the popular tourist destination in the Islands is "love beach", also called the "hidden beach". It’s entirely hidden, and can only be reached by swimming through a short, narrow tunnel. While the beach itself is natural, the sinkhole is reportedly man-made. The Mexican government started using the islands as target practice prior to the First World War. These controlled bombings have formed numerous sinkholes. So, most likely a natural cave roof is collapsed due to bombings.

📽 @postandfly
📍Marieta islands, Mexico
🎶 Gustavo Bravetti - Babel
